In Short:


Product designed to cut a cylindrical glass bottles in straight cuts up to size for 3 litre jars. Give the second life for used vine, beer, vodka and more glass bottles just by slicing them in half and more – the only limitation is your imagination. Promote green mind-set by recycling used glass bottles! About Us and Our Idea:Everything started with a bottle of beer in our hands while watching TV and few more bottles laying around in the kitchen next to the bin… No, we are not untidy guys, we just love beer.So who are we  - two old friends with a common vision for recycling used glass bottles and jars. While one of us is more in DIY and crafts and the other in engineering and construction we stumbled upon a solution how to give the second chance for used glass bottles without just throwing them in recycling bins.Cutting glass is not as complex as it might seem. The nature has already done it easy for us - the glass crystal structure is organized in straight parallels and perpendiculars, the only necessary action is to give a “kick” (not an actual kick, but you know what I mean) in right direction to unleash these “natural” lines for our favor.Once you can split the bottle in half there are more opportunities how to use it than when it was in a single piece – more cuts-> more pieces-> more opportunities. The only thing that needs to be done by you right now is to unleash your imagination to the maximum and see where your bottle cutter will lead you to. While it was just a side project for our own good, we received more and more positive reviews from our friends and colleges who occasionally received our glass gifts. We decided to share with our product also with other people! We need your support in order to start up a large quantity manufacturing program We are really inspired by our product and we are eager to proceed with manufacturing as soon as possible to deliver the product to you – our beloved Kickstarters.What is „cut A bottle”:“cut A bottle” is innovative cylindrically shaped glass bottle cutter intended for DIY projects and home use. Our main getaways for the product is 1-2-3 step procedure, effortless cutting, and “cut A bottle” is fit to operate with different size both bottles and jars to fit in its movable “traps”. It does not take too much space, nor weights a ton – it is completely opposite - “cut A bottle” weights less than 500 grams or in imperial scale less than 1.1 pounds. When not in use it can be beautifully stored either horizontally just over shelf or vertically even as a book stand for your home library. The only limitation to the possible outcomes of your own DIY project is your own creativity and imagination, but here are some tips what you can produce yourself with our product - glasses, vases, candle sticks, lamp globes, ashtrays, even aquariums, Christmas decors and flowerpots….and this is not a full list, there is much more you can create out of used bottles with it! The Manufacturing:As much this part might be the most boring part for non-technical people, we think it is important to describe the whole process how the actual product is made and how we can guarantee the precision!First of all we are using high quality plywood to start with removed branches so the base material is all through consistent. As for cutting technology we are using laser cutting technology, which can perform with ultra-high precision – the error margin for the laser cutter is 0.0254 millimetres or in imperial value - 0.001 inches, thus close to nothing. All the assembling and gluing part for the actual unit is handwork with standardized test trials for each and every unit to ensure the high quality standard before shipping it out to you – Kickstarters.From Baby Steps to “Cut A Bottle”: Little background on how we developed our “cut A bottle” device. First there was a problem - isn’t there a better solution for used glass bottles rather than just plain recycling? As we discovered later – yes, there is! Starting from cost nothing vases for flowers, drinking glasses, candle tarries, ashtrays, simple glasses for sopping dirty brushes, small home decors and on and on…  We have tried different bottle cutting techniques, but each and single one was not without flaws – starting from burning rope till metal wire - none of them was as precise as cutting with carbonite knifes. SO knowing what is the best for glass we had to come up with a “machine” how to do it. First prototype as we called it ”the Beast” was not as accurate as we would have hoped for, but as far as it goes the whole device was not made entirely accurate up to task too. Thus, there were more flimsy and wavy cuts as we hoped for, but the whole concept did work– the bottles were cut! Back to the drawing board.Second prototype as we called it “the Intellectual” displayed aristocrat design patterns and was created with the accuracy that we were aiming for, successful site testing was done with less and less variables this time. As far as the bottles could be cut in perfect straight lines now, there were some minor bugs that we wanted to address before producing the final products, that could be only discovered throughout this site testing.Third and final prototype as we call it “the Real Deal” performed in previously set guidelines – easy to use, more possibilities for a knife to be located and operated, more support points for bottles, more rigid construction due to the extra support walls, fixed cutting position, less pressure needed for user to apply for cutting, even the kids could do it. The cuts are straight as knife, the technique for separating has been developed up to the perfection, and the most important fact is that it is as simple as possible from users’ perspective. Now we have the “ready to manufacture” final product for you.NB! Of course due to the fact that the glass pieces before sanding can be extremely sharp, we DO NOT ADVISE TO ALLOW THE KIDS TO OPERATE THE “CUT A BOTTLE” PRODUCT WITHOUT SUPERVISION OF ADULTS AT ALL TIME.What Is In The Kit:What we want to deliver to our Kickstarter supporters is a ready to start “cut A bottle” Kit including all the necessary features and items to start to use the product as soon as you have opened the box.
One "cut A bottle” wooden base unit with its movable side walls;
Carbonite blade cutting tool containing turnable 6 blade set;
One easily adjustable strap for correctly positioning the bottle in the cutter;
One rubber band for ensuring the pressure diversification all around the bottle for more accurate cuts.
3 different grit size sandpapers included in the kit (60, 120, 180)
 How to use:Cutting a bottle is an easy 1-2-3 step procedure.Ok, actually it’s a 1-2-3-4 step process if you count in consuming the bottle’s contents first, but this would not be the hardest part to start with, wouldn’t it?1.Scoring: While the product is called a bottle cutter it does not actually cut the bottle. The tool is meant to create a score line on the bottle at the location you wish to cut the bottle. You simply need to align the cutter to place where you want to cut the bottle, tighten it to create a snug fit and slowly rotate the bottle, while you should make one full circle around the bottle with evenly distributed down force while rotating. You should hear the glass cutter scratching the glass surface. The score line should be slightly seen, but continuous all around the bottle.2.Separation: There are many videos on the internet showing different methods to separate the two sections of the bottle, but after trying them all, the method that produces the most consistent results is simply to use the hot water (doing this over a kitchen sink is recommended). Boil some water and pour it evenly over the score line, not too much. After a few seconds, use a tap to pour cold water over the same score line. This cycle of hot and cold will cause the bottle to crack along the score line. The bottle should separate after one or 2 cycles of hot and cold, thicker glass may take additional cycles though.3.Sanding: After splitting the bottle there is a sharp edge on both halves. Finish the sharp glass edge using the recommended sandpapers. There are three different grit size sandpapers included in the kit (60, 120, 180). You should start with 60 grit sandpaper, which will remove the sharp edge fast. For smoother result use 120 and 180 grit sandpaper accordingly. After using the 180 grit sandpaper the edge is perfectly smooth for simple use. If you still want it smoother, you can buy a higher grit sandpaper at your local construction depo.Green Mind-Set:With our product you would be recycling the same amount of the glass as before, but this time you would be giving the second life for the glass right away without any special treatment needed before. Thus, reducing the need of industrial recycling and giving the glass the second chance right away is a real resource saver. Thinking green had never been so easy and fun just by giving a second life to empty bottles and creating your environment all around more creative and vivid at once!Imagination Is the Limit:            What You’ll Get for Backing Us:
For £25 - One “cut A bottle” Early Bird Edition Kit. Be the first one receiving your own “cut A bottle” unit before everyone else for discounted price! Only 100 units! Delivered in March.

For £30 - One “cut A bottle” Regular Kit. Be the second one receiving your own “cut A bottle” unit before New Year for regular price. Unlimited amount. Delivered in April-May (Early delivery only applies for European Union countries, for rest of the world the product will be delivered on May)Levels:

Elegance is a personal manner. We want you to choose the design that best represents who you are. Each strap has a unique style and adapts to a particular type of user. From classic to casual, and for those who are always in a hurry. We strongly believe that our customers contribute to the definition of our value proposition. That's why we want to let you choose how to combine your favourite case with the strap that you prefer. You can choose among a wide range of straps of different colors:

ROPE: Salmon Pink//Blue Navy//Green Tiffany//Black 'Seppia'

LEATHER: Brown 'Testa di Moro' or 'Crocodile'//Black 'Nappa' or 'Crocodile'

MILANESE MASH: Gold//Silver//Black
  When we started this project our long term goal was to reduce the environmental impact of our production process.  Since this is not something you can achieve from a day to the other, we also meant to find a way to leave an immediate footprint. That's when our partnerships with NGOs that have been helping the planet for decades kicked in. Every different model of our new collection is linked to a different environmental campaign ran by one of our partners.   Carolina, our designer, has studied for years the cultural-aesthetic figures of Italian design and the great humanistic tradition of Italy at the faculty of design of Genoa. Her Italian cultural background provided her an early passion for Italian fashion designers, from the trailblazing giants who built the great fashion empires, with their unmethodical and emotional character, to the independents who march to the beats of their own drums and represent tomorrow’s innovators.  From this combination of Italian tradition and contemporary propulsion, the concept of Bacàn design arose with an environmentally friendly approach in an attempt of conciliating “la bella figura” with the challenges of the future.    SPECIFICATIONS: 
 Watch case: zinc alloy, stainless steel;
 Dial colours: gold, silver, blue navy, bordeaux, black, green;
 Water resistant: 3 ATM, 30 meters;
 Glass: high quality crystal;
 Strap size: 18 mm for him, best fit for 14 - 23 cm wrist; 16 mm for her;
 Date: 31 days; 
 Watch size (diameter / thickness): 
- Bacàn Square for Him - 36 / 9 mm;- Bacàn Square for Her – 28.6 / 9 mm;
 Weight (with strap): 35 - 57g;
 Movement: VJ34 SEIKO (battery included);
 Strap: genuine leather, braided rope elastic with brown genuine leather finish, milan mash;
- Available genuine leather strap colours: brown mahogany, croco brown mahogany, black; nappa, croco black nappa;- Available braided rope elastic strap colours: blue navy, salmon pink, green tiffany, black nappa; - Available milan mash strap colours: gold, silver, black nappa; Warranty: 2 years limited warranty against manufacturing defects.  Our business model consists of the manufacture and sale of highly stylish watches, without charging the luxury mark-up. By skipping the traditional channels of distribution and making improvements of efficiency, we are able to re-invest part of our profits in the creation of a sustainable supply chain. The first steps we are going to move in order to reduce the environmental impact of our watch are going to be the use of high-quality materials and the requirement of certificates of social and environmental sustainability of our suppliers.  Before being colleagues, we are friends. We are a team of students from Genoa (Italy) who share common values and interests: design, care for the environment, politics, internet.The idea of the value proposition of our campaign  was born in the library of the university of economics of our city. We were discussing about the political responses to the threats posed by global warming, and we all agreed that we don’t believe to the lies of those who claim that climate change is an invention in order to raise their electoral consensus. Therefore, we tried to find out how to conjugate our business with this important issue.Our answer? Bacàn Square, the watch that saves the planet.
